last_episode_to_air.overview: Brad and Anna are looking for a log cabin in the countryside of southwestern Pennsylvania, but need a commute under 30 minutes; she would like an open kitchen and they both want private acreage where they can explore and let their dogs run free.

name: Log Cabin Living
overview: Follow one family as they ditch the hustle and bustle and go on a journey to find the quintessential escape in Log Cabin Living . They'll navigate this unusual real estate market as they search for their perfect log home retreat.

episodes.name: Montana Log Cabin
episodes.overview: Lance and Melissa Fahrney, along with their four children, are trading in the hot, humid beaches of Florida for a chance at log cabin living in Montana. They're searching for a basecamp that opens the door to a world of outdoor recreational opportunities they can't experience in Florida skiing, sledding, and hiking in the mountains. The Fahrneys are dreaming of a secluded log cabin, nestled in the woods and close to a big lake. Real estate agent David Fetveit will help them find their new log cabin living situation around the Flathead Lake area in northwestern Montana.

episodes.name: Blue Ridge Cabin Quest
episodes.overview: An Atlanta couple is tired of living near loud highways and hopes to find a log cabin in quaint Blue Ridge, Georgia. They're hoping to find a cabin with enough space to host friends and family, close access to outdoor recreation and a fantastic view of the Blue Ridge Mountains for under $350,000.

episodes.name: Hawaiian Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: A couple has set down roots on the island of Oahu and are looking for a bigger home with the comforts of a country log cabin for their three growing kids. They hope to find a cabin with a yard for the family dog and the backdrop of mountain views and ocean sounds. With a budget of $850,000 on an expensive island where log cabins are a rarity, they have their work cut out for them.

episodes.name: Massachusetts Cabin Search
episodes.overview: High school sweethearts from Greenville, MA, are ready to upgrade to a log cabin where they can raise their growing family. They're searching for a secluded area where the kids can play that's also close to town amenities and their families. With a realtor in the family, the couple is getting some help finding their dream log cabin but will they be able to find something they can afford?

episodes.name: North Georgia Cabin Search
episodes.overview: A couple and their two sons that love to experience the outdoors are ready to ditch Atlanta's skyscrapers for the beautiful mountains of north Georgia. They are on the hunt for a cabin and hope to find one with a perfect kitchen, wraparound porch and stunning views of the mountains.

episodes.name: Maggie Valley Cabin Search
episodes.overview: After spending three years on assignment in Shanghai, a couple looks to slow their pace and buy a log cabin in Maggie Valley, North Carolina. They're hoping to find a rustic log cabin in the Smoky Mountains with easy winter access, but can their realtor find an ideal option that meets all of their needs?

episodes.name: Vail Valley Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: In Colorado's Vail Valley, a young couple looks for their first home together. They want easy access to all their favorite outdoor activities, including skiing, biking and hiking with their dogs, and they need extra space for entertaining guests. They hope their $900,000 budget helps them find a log home with privacy, spectacular views and a yard for the dogs.

episodes.name: Cozy Vermont Cabin
episodes.overview: Ryan, Tara and their sports-minded sons are looking for the perfect log cabin in Vermont. They want an authentic log cabin with enough land to raise chickens and plant a garden. Even though New England is known more for Colonial houses than log cabins, they're determined to find a cozy cabin deep in the forests of the Green Mountain State.

episodes.name: Tennessee Homestead Cabin
episodes.overview: An outdoors-loving family of three in Tennessee is looking for a secluded log cabin with space to entertain friends and plenty of land to homestead like their ancestors. They enjoy hunting, gunsmithing, four-wheeling and foraging for wild mushrooms. With a budget of $550,000, they hope to find the perfect forever log cabin with sufficient flat land for their homesteading plans.

episodes.name: New Hampshire Cabin Getaway
episodes.overview: A couple of Boston outdoor enthusiasts are ready to expand their family in a log cabin in the mountains of New Hampshire. The White Mountains area offers all the things they love do year-round from skiing and snowmobiling to hiking and fishing. They're seeking a cabin with updated features in a low-maintenance setting so they can spend time doing the recreational activities they love. They've enlisted a local agent to help them out but can he find them a good match within their budget?

episodes.name: Mount Hood Village Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: After recently moving to the States, a nature-loving British family wants to buy a log cabin in the Mount Hood Village area of Oregon. With a strict budget of $550,000, they're hoping to find a place with plenty of seclusion, amazing views and a quick walk to the river for fishing.

episodes.name: North Carolina Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: A couple in Morrisville, North Carolina, hopes to find a log home with enough land to expand their family business near the eastern lake region of Raleigh. They want enough room for their whole family plus some space separate from the main living spaces for a home office. Will she find the space she wants for their daughters or will he get the final say on a detached garage for work projects?

episodes.name: Shenandoah Dream Cabin
episodes.overview: Pennsylvania natives are ready to purchase a log cabin at one of their favorite spots in the Shenandoah Valley. The mountains will provide the perfect backdrop for the active family's favorite activities including hiking, canoeing and exploring nature. They're hoping to find a log home surrounded by wilderness where they can entertain friends and family near the river. Can their local realtor find a log cabin that fulfills all their wishes?

episodes.name: Escape to the Poconos
episodes.overview: Busy parents of three children search for a getaway in the Pocono Mountains where they can unplug and reconnect as a family. They hope to find a log cabin in the woods near a ski hill and other outdoor activities for $325,000.

episodes.name: Washington Log Home Hunt
episodes.overview: An outdoorsy Seattle couple wants to escape their busy city life and move to a log cabin in a quiet, peaceful setting. They'd like a body of water on the property as well as a shop for their glassblowing studio, but it needs to be close enough to commute back to the city for work. Helping them in their cabin search is a childhood friend, who's tagging along to offer support and suggestions.

episodes.name: Phoenix Foothills Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: A couple looks for a log cabin getaway in the mountains of Arizona. They're hoping to get their busy family of six to relax and enjoy riding ATVs in the small town of Payson, AZ. He would love a cabin with a rustic mountain feel while she's looking for a spacious setting where they can host family and friends. With the help of a local realtor, they hope to find the perfect retreat from the heat of the city.

episodes.name: North Georgia Vacation Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: Four best friends from Florida are looking for something different, so they're buying a log cabin together in Mineral Bluff, GA. Along with their realtor, they hope to find a cabin that can accommodate their two families and has plenty of room for their children to play outside.

episodes.name: Big Bear Lake Cabin Getaway
episodes.overview: An active and outdoorsy family of five is looking for a log cabin getaway from their home in Carlsbad, CA, to the rustic mountains destination of Big Bear Lake. They're looking for a home away from home where they can sit back, relax and enjoy the mountain views during any season. But with a modest budget and a tight real estate market, they may have to make some sacrifices.

episodes.name: Central Virginia Log Home
episodes.overview: A family of four is looking to move from their current home in the city of Lynchburg, VA, to the nearby countryside where they will have more room to explore and become immersed in nature. He grew up visiting his grandmother in her log cabin and wants his children to have that experience as well. She's hoping to find a home with an updated kitchen and an open concept, and he's looking for a detached garage. It's a hefty wish list but their realtor is ready to help them find the perfect log home.

episodes.name: Upper Peninsula Log Cabin Retreat
episodes.overview: A military woman loves the traveling lifestyle of her career, but misses her family and her childhood spent in the Upper Peninsula of Michigan. She enlists her best friend from high school to help her in her search for a home base where she will eventually settle after military life. She wants a cabin out of town with some acreage, yet still in close proximity to friends and family. The friends team up with a local realtor to find her perfect log home.

episodes.name: Winding Down on Mount Lemmon
episodes.overview: A Tucson couple wants a cabin retreat in Mount Lemmon, AZ, where they can hike with their dogs, rock climb and relax while enjoying each other's company. They rarely have time for travel due to busy lives in the medical field, so they hope to find a secluded spot with classic mountain views where they can find a balance.

episodes.name: Minnesota Great Plains Cabin
episodes.overview: A young Minnesota family is ready to settle down and grow in a small town cabin. They're hoping to find a home with enough bedrooms for them to expand into and enough acreage for their kids to ditch technology and explore nature. Their budget may force them to search outside of their target area, but their family real estate agent is ready to help them find the perfect log cabin.

episodes.name: New Hampshire Log Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: A couple seeks a lakeside cabin in the New Hampshire countryside for extended family gatherings. They want something with a rustic woodwork aesthetic that has a modern kitchen and a lawn for their two boys to play on.

episodes.name: Fannin County Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: Florida empty nesters decide to escape the city life and head into the heart of the Blue Ridge Mountains of Northern Georgia. They love the small-town feel and are looking forward to exploring the town, meeting new people and introducing their children to the mountains when they visit. They hope to find a cabin with an open floor plan that's near the water and their agent is on board to help them find the perfect place.

episodes.name: Colorado Dream Cabin
episodes.overview: A Houston, Texas, couple looks for a spacious, rustic home in Colorado to raise their kids without the hustle and bustle of a big city. They set their sights on Woodland Park, but with a highly competitive real estate market, it may prove difficult to find their forever home with the perfect view.

episodes.name: Colorado Cabin Quest Along the Rocky Mountain Foothills
episodes.overview: A city-dwelling couple wants to trade bumper-to-bumper traffic for a home where they can raise their two kids immersed in nature seven days a week. They look in the foothills surrounding the little mining town of Cripple Creek for a log cabin complete with plenty of space for their family and classic Colorado Rocky Mountain views.

episodes.name: Arizona Mountain Cabin Getaway
episodes.overview: A Scottsdale, Arizona, family is looking for a log cabin getaway in a cooler, mountainous part of Arizona where they can experience all four seasons. He has his heart set on an A-frame style cabin with giant windows to let in all the natural light, and she wants plenty of outdoor space to entertain.

episodes.name: All In A Hard Days Work
episodes.overview: A couple from Maryville, Tennessee, is on the hunt for a cabin where they can get their hands dirty and grow their own food. They hope to find a cabin with breathtaking views and a spacious kitchen, with plenty of acreage to share with their four kids.

episodes.name: Wisconsin Lakeside Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: A couple and their young daughters search for their dream cabin in America's Dairyland. They're looking for a log home with a lake access and room for family and friends to visit in the quaint town of Mauston, Wisconsin.

episodes.name: Taking Time to Relax
episodes.overview: A house-flipping couple from middle Tennessee is looking to escape the city and set down roots in the log cabin of their dreams. They want a place where they can practice music, archery and enjoy the quiet while remaining close enough to the music scene in Nashville.

episodes.name: Getting Closer to Family
episodes.overview: A California couple wants to find a new home closer to her Nebraska hometown. After discovering Evergreen, Colorado, and all its recreational opportunities, the couple and their three kids are ready to find their forever cabin in the foothills of the Rocky Mountains.

episodes.name: Alaska Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: A couple and their three-year-old daughter search for a cabin with unparalleled views and access to the great outdoors near Fairbanks, Alaska.

episodes.name: A New Life in Washington
episodes.overview: A recently engaged couple is moving from Missouri to Washington to start their new life together. They want a cabin that has a short commute to Spokane for work and is close to outdoor activities so they can be active with their dogs.

episodes.name: Reconnecting in Garden Valley, Idaho
episodes.overview: A couple decides to ditch their fast-paced lives in Boise, ID, for a move to Garden Valley. With so many outdoor activities in the area, they feel it's the perfect place to escape and reconnect as a family. She wants a cabin with large windows that let in natural light, and he's looking for a property with a low-maintenance yard.

episodes.name: Rustic Georgia Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: A couple with a toddler and another on the way goes on the hunt for a cozy log cabin near the Blue Ridge Mountains. They hope to find the perfect getaway in the quiet and quaint town of Ellijay, Georgia.

episodes.name: Reliving A Country Childhood
episodes.overview: Newlyweds who spent their childhoods in the country long to return; in Rhode Island, they look for a cabin with some land where they can reconnect with nature and their dogs have plenty of room to explore.

episodes.name: Growing A Family's Forever Home
episodes.overview: A couple hunt for a unique log cabin in southern Connecticut where they can raise their young daughters; in addition to the New England forest and array of outdoor activities, he wants land for privacy and hunting while she wants an updated kitchen.

episodes.name: Recapturing Family Time
episodes.overview: In Louisville, Ky., a couple and their two children search for a cabin; she wants to raise the children in a small town, where they can roam on their own land and spend quality time as a family.

episodes.name: Massachusetts Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: An active couple wants to ditch the city and get back to nature with a rustic log cabin retreat outside of Boston; the first-time home buyers want plenty of room for a dog and easy access to their favorite outdoor activities.

episodes.name: Vermont Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: A couple combs the hills of central Vermont for a one-of-a-kind cabin to raise their son in. They're looking for a turnkey home with rustic charm that has two full bathrooms, a spacious kitchen and plenty of acreage for the family to enjoy.

episodes.name: Kentucky Country Cabin Search
episodes.overview: Texas newlyweds are relocating to northern Kentucky and looking to settle down and find a rustic log cabin in the country; she wants a property with acreage to ride her horse; he wants a quiet environment to relax and unwind at the end of a workday.

episodes.overview: A couple is looking to escape the hustle and bustle of the Phoenix Metro area for a quiet slice of country life in Show Low, Arizona. After years of bringing their five children up to the area to visit, they are looking forward to purchasing a spacious log cabin in the White Mountains that has a secluded feel but is still close to town.

episodes.name: Carolina Cabin Chase
episodes.overview: A couple and their two young children are on the search for a log cabin in High Point, North Carolina, where they can unwind in the solitude of nature as a family. They want a cabin with plenty of outdoor space for the kids to explore, plenty of indoor space to host family and a garage big enough to store a boat.

episodes.name: High Country Hideaway
episodes.overview: A Florida couple is on the hunt for a cozy log cabin in Boone, North Carolina, where they can reconnect with their roots and create lasting memories for their children. Eager to escape the heat and hustle of Florida city life, he wants long range mountain views that North Carolina's high country is known for, and she would love a cabin with rustic style.

episodes.name: Secluded in Park City, Utah
episodes.overview: A Seattle family fell in love with Park City, Utah, after moving to the small mountain town for work. They love the outdoor lifestyle and they're looking for a unique and secluded cabin where they can grow as a family. She needs a home office and he needs plenty of space to play with the kids.

episodes.name: Family Time in the Teton Range
episodes.overview: A couple is on the hunt for a mountain escape where they can spend time with their kids and enjoy Eastern Idaho's outdoor activities. In addition to privacy and water views, they hope to find a place with trail access and a large living space where the family can gather.

episodes.overview: Engaged homebuyers search for their first home together on the outskirts of Wausau, Wisconsin, where they both work. They love being surrounded by nature and want to find a cabin that brings a rustic, outdoor feel inside and provides respite from the workday grind of the city.

episodes.name: Finding A North Carolina Cabin
episodes.overview: A couple and their two children are searching for their dream log cabin near Boone, North Carolina, so they can explore the numerous hiking trails, city parks and local college sporting events.

episodes.name: White Mountains Cabin Hunt
episodes.overview: A couple wants to move far from the suburbs of Ohio to a place where they can enjoy the outdoors in their backyard, away from the hustle and bustle of the city. They're looking for a peaceful cabin in the Knox County area where she can start a garden and he can practice his woodworking.

episodes.overview: Colorado natives Darrell and Becky are looking for a log cabin in the Blue Ridge Mountains of North Carolina. Living in South Carolina for a few years has made them miss the mountains, so they'd like to find a cabin with a spectacular view to enjoy from a wraparound porch. Becky grew up in a log cabin and wants a place where their family can gather, spend holidays and continue to make memories in the years to come. The couple is focusing their search for their dream cabin in the Mars Hill and Wolf Laurel areas north of Asheville.

episodes.overview: A couple wants to move far from the suburbs of Ohio to a place where they can enjoy the outdoors in their backyard, away from the hustle and bustle of the city; they are looking for a peaceful cabin in the Knox County area.
